similarity
Class Similarity

java.lang.Object
  similarity.Similarity

public class Similarity
extends java.lang.Object

This class is used for calculating similarity between two vectors, finding the closest vector within a library of vectors and such, it can be used for any distance metric calculations

Author:
Barkin Aygun

calculateSimilarity

public static double calculateSimilarity(double[] vec1,
                                         double[] vec2,
                                         int type)
Calculates similarity of type given between two vectors
COSINE similarity - normalized dot product L2 metric - root of sum of squares of differences L1 metric - sum of differences

Parameters:
vec1 - Array of doubles for first vector
vec2 - Array of doubles for second vector
type - Distance Metric for similarity (COSINE/L1/L2)
Returns:
the distance between the two vectors

similarVectors

public static int[] similarVectors(double[][] vectors,
                                   int index,
                                   int type)
Finds the most similar vector to the given index vector in the vectors using the given distance metric, returns the indexes of vectors in descending order, closest first

Parameters:
vectors - 2-D array of doubles representing all vectors
index - Index of the vector to find most similar to
type - Distance metric
Returns:
array of integers of indices of closest to furthest vector
